Add the missing Drupal\Core\Url import to WidgetPluginBase.

The facets.block.ajax branch in WidgetPluginBase::build() calls
`new Url($route_name, $route_params, $options)`, but the file only
imports Drupal\Core\Link. PHP therefore resolves the unqualified name
against the current namespace and fatals with:

  Error: Class "Drupal\facets\Widget\Url" not found in
  Drupal\facets\Widget\WidgetPluginBase->Drupal\facets\Widget\{closure}()
  (line 63 of src/Widget/WidgetPluginBase.php)

Present in every 2.0.x release including 2.0.10 and 2.0.x HEAD. The
block was removed outright in 3.0.x, so there is nothing to backport.

diff --git a/src/Widget/WidgetPluginBase.php b/src/Widget/WidgetPluginBase.php
--- a/src/Widget/WidgetPluginBase.php
+++ b/src/Widget/WidgetPluginBase.php
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@
 use Drupal\Core\Form\FormStateInterface;
 use Drupal\Core\Link;
 use Drupal\Core\Plugin\PluginBase;
+use Drupal\Core\Url;
 use Drupal\facets\FacetInterface;
 use Drupal\facets\Result\Result;
 use Drupal\facets\Result\ResultInterface;
